===Etymology===
From Russian '''[[царь]]''' ''(tsar’),'' from Old Russian '''[[цьсарь]]''' ''(tsĭsarĭ),'' from Old Church Slavonic '''[[цѣсарь]]''' ''(tsěsarĭ),'' believed to come from Latin '''[[Caesar]]'''.

===Alternative spellings===
*[[czar]]
*[[tzar]]

